    Impact of belimumab on organ damage in systemic lupus erythematosus.
Long-term belimumab use in SLE also reduced organ damage progression measured by the Systemic Lupus International Collaborating Clinics/American College of Rheumatology Damage Index (SDI), as reported in open-label extension studies, and propensity score-matched comparative analyses to background therapy alone. Results from a clinical trial showed that in patients with active LN, belimumab treatment improved renal response, reduced the risk of renal-related events and impacted features related to kidney damage progression, compared with background therapy alone. The decrease of organ damage accumulation observed with belimumab treatment in SLE, including LN, suggest a disease-modifying effect.
